> 
> I'd like to get some feedback from listees on a car
> purchase my wife and I will be facing within the next
> few months. I don't think we will be seriously looking
> at leasing a vehicle but purchasing instead.
> 
> We will be replacing our primary automobile (1994
> Pontiac Bonneville with 103,000 miles).
> 
> My wife and I historically keep cars a long time. We
> have never sold a car with less than 100K on it. We
> also have an 87 Nissan Sentra with 136K on it and a
> 1972 VW Beetle with 99,700 miles on it (will never
> sell!!!). We will likely sell the Sentra and I will
> drive the Bonneville and my wife will drive the car we
> purchase.
> 
> My question has to do with the tradeoff of buying a
> new vehicle and the accompanying big first year
> depreciation as opposed to say a used car coming off a
> lease with say 25,000 miles on it.
> 
> Obviously if we were planning to sell the car after
> 3-4 years, then the precipitous drop in value after
> the first year might be important but since we hold
> the car a long time, would we be better off just
> buying a new one with low miles?
> 
> I'm sure there are a number of other things to
> consider but I'm predominantly interested in feedback
> from listees on the new vs. used issue.
> 
> FWIW, we will be looking at mid to full size 4 dr.
> sedans like Nissan Altima and Maxima, VW Passat,
> Pontiac Bonneville and Grand Prix, Toyota Camry and
> Avalon, Mazda 626 and Millenia. May look at Volvos but
> they may be out of price range.
> 
> If listees have any advice on brands and models they
> have had good experience with, I'd welcome the
> comments.
> 
> Thanks for feedback.
